    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is a driver-spec 2002 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L straight-six power plant. This naturally aspirated engine utilizes six individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing to produce a broad, linear power band. Power is routed through a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission to a variable M differential lock. Significant preventive maintenance has been addressed, including a comprehensive rear subframe reinforcement and a VANOS system overhaul to mitigate common S54 failure points. The chassis retains its factory-tuned MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension geometry, delivering exceptional lateral stability and communicative steering rack feedback. While the exterior displays minor patina consistent with its 'good' condition rating, the mechanical vitals and drivetrain synchronization are sharp, making this a premier candidate for the purist seeking a visceral, analog driving experience.",
      "price": 31500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
